<Color(-34022)>Learn Your Structures</Color><Color(-154)>Arcana Stones</Color>  You and your opponent each have three of these immobile crystals on  the playing field. Shatter all of your enemy's Arcana Stones to claim  victory.<Color(-154)>Gates</Color>  Minions will appear in front of your currently selected gate.  Returning minions to a gate area will restore their HP.  Minions can still be summoned from a destroyed gate, but they will be  unable to exit the gate area. Conversely, minions outside a destroyed  gate will be unable to enter.<Color(-154)>Search Eye</Color>  This structure reveals your opponent's minions. If the Search Eye is  destroyed, you will only be able to see enemy units that are near  your own minions.<Color(-154)>Shield</Color>  This structure adds defensive strength to Arcana Stones. Destroy the  enemy Shield and your opponent's Arcana Stones will be more easily  shattered.<Color(-34022)>Structural Regeneration</Color>  All structures except for Arcana Stones can only be temporarily  destroyed. Their various functions will reactivate at full strength  after a certain amount of time has passed.  ※Positioning your minions near a destroyed structure will hasten  　the reactivation process.<Color(-34022)>Play to Your Minions' Strengths</Color>  Each variety of minion is capable of inflicting greater damage against  certain structures. Learn each unit's strengths, and pick the right  minion for the job!<Color(-34022)>Turn the Tide with Special Actions</Color>  These conditions must be met before a special action can be used:  ・Four minions of the same variety are gathered in an action party  ・Each minion in the action party has full action points   (Action points accumulate over time)  To perform a special action, select an individual minion from the  action party, and press the Execute Action button on the minion  hotbar.<Color(-34022)>Mastering Traps</Color>  Some minions will place traps with their special actions. A trap will  become armed ten seconds after it has been placed, and it can then  be triggered by pressing the Trigger Trap button on the minion  hotbar.  ※Only one trap can be placed at a time.<If(GreaterThan(PlayerParameter(80),0))><Color(-34022)>Playing with a <If(GreaterThan(PlayerParameter(75),0))>Controller<Else/>Gamepad</If></Color><Color(-154)>Selecting Minions</Color> Recorder settings are enabled.　2. Current duty is available for recording.　3. Parties meet minimum size requirements.　4. Record ready check has been executed.<Color(-287193856)>1. Recorder settings are enabled</Color>Recorder settings can be adjusted under <Color(-34022)>Duty Recorder</Color> in the main menu.<Color(-287193856)>2. Current duty is available for recording</Color>Not all duties are available for recording.Recordable duties are marked with a special icon.<Color(-287193856)>3. Parties meet minimum size requirements</Color>Duties undertaken by undersized parties cannot be recorded.※This includes parties formed via the Duty Finder.<Color(-287193856)>4. Record ready check has been executed</Color>Approval from all party members is required before recording can begin.※Record ready checks must be performed within 5 minutes of commencing a duty.Only 3 records may be saved at once. Oldest records will be overwritten.––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––<Color(-287193856)>Viewing Recorded Duties</Color>The following conditions must be met to view duty records:　1. You are in an inn room.　2. Recorded duty is from the most recent game version.<Color(-287193856)>1. You are in an inn room</Color>Duty playback is only available in inn rooms.<Color(-287193856)>2. Recorded duty is from the most recent game version</Color>This includes both major updates and minor hotfixes.Recordings will become inaccessible after applying the newest data patch.

Speed</Color>Change playback speed to 1x, 2x, or 4x of the original.<Color(-287193856)>Chapter Selection</Color>Start playback at the position selected.※Depending on chapter position, playback may not be instantaneous.<Color(-287193856)>Next Chapter</Color>Skip to the next available chapter.<Color(-287193856)>Previous Chapter</Color>Skip to the previous chapter.<Color(-287193856)>HUD Display</Color>Toggle on/off on-screen UI elements.※Settings are saved for next playback.<Color(-287193856)>Focus Target</Color>Camera can be focused on any party member.<Color(-287193856)>Group Pose</Color>Open the Group Pose function.※This feature is not always available.<Color(-287193856)>Idling Camera</Color>Activate idling camera.※This feature is not always available.
